cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for learning network representations in dynamic networks, which is a fundamental task in many graph applications. The method uses autoencoders to embed graph snapshots based on their local structure and can also learn temporal dependencies by collaborating with other autoencoders. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers on the development of algorithms and models for machine learning, which is the main focus of the proposed method.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers papers on the analysis and modeling of social and information networks, which are examples of dynamic networks that the proposed method can be applied to.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): This sub-category covers papers on the development of software systems and tools, which may be relevant to the implementation of the proposed method.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category covers papers on the design and analysis of data structures and algorithms, which may be relevant to the computational aspects of the proposed method.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers papers on the development and application of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which are relevant to the autoencoder-based approach used in the proposed method.
